{
  "texts": [
    "It is through habit that humans engage in moral practice.",
    "Moreover, two capacities are highly related to habit-impulse and intelligence.",
    "Impulse, as an emotional faculty, drives the adjustment of habits, serving as an agency of deviation to give new directions to old habits and change their quality (Dewey, 2008b, p. 67).",
    "Intelligence refers to rational faculties such as observation, memory, and judgment.",
    "Habits are not innate: they initially resemble instincts and are refined into new habits through adjustment."
  ]
}